## Rule 8 — Complete `AppRouteMeta` Field Reference

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `title` | `string` | Page title |
| `titleKey` | `string` | i18n key |
| `parent` | `LayoutMode` | Layout shell |
| `rank` | `number` | Sidebar order weight |
| `roles` | `string[]` | Role-level route guard |
| `auths` | `string[]` | Permission-level guard |
| `keepAlive` | `boolean` | Cache component |
| `icon` | `string` | Menu icon |
| `showLink` | `boolean` | Sidebar visibility |
| `hidden` | `boolean` | Hide route entirely |
| `hideBreadcrumb` | `boolean` | Hide breadcrumb |
| `fixedTag` | `boolean` | Pin tab |
| `hiddenTag` | `boolean` | Hide tab |
| `activeMenu` | `string` | Sidebar active menu path |
| `isLink` | `boolean` | External URL route |
| `linkUrl` | `string` | External URL |
| `reuseWindow` | `boolean` | Reuse window |
| `backstage` | `boolean` | Backend-sourced marker |
| `ratio` | `string` | Ratio layout value |
| `parentPaths` | `string[]` | Ancestor paths |
| `transition` | `RouteTransition` | Page enter/leave transition; SSOT `src/types/modules/router.d.ts`, runtime `AnimateRouterView` |

### `transition` — `RouteTransition`

**SSOT:** `src/types/modules/router.d.ts` (`RouteTransition`, `CssTime`, `PhaseValue`). **Runtime:** `src/layouts/components/AnimateRouterView.vue`. Transitions apply only when the layout store has route transitions enabled (`enableTransition`).

#### Priority and mutual exclusion

1. **Class mode (animate.css):** If `enterClass` and/or `leaveClass` is set, `<Transition>` uses active classes, `type` is `animation`, and **`meta.transition.name` is ignored** (no named transition).
2. **Named CSS transition mode:** Otherwise, transition name resolves in order: `meta.transition.name` → `layoutStore.transitionName` → `'cinematic-fade'`.
3. **`mode`:** `undefined` defaults to `'out-in'` at runtime. Use `'default'` to omit the `mode` prop (Vue’s default behavior).
4. **`appear`:** When transitions are enabled, `appear` is **on** unless explicitly set to `false`.

#### CSS variables and timing

- **Global** `duration` / `delay` (string `CssTime`): set on the wrapper as `--route-transition-duration`, `--animate-duration`, `--route-transition-delay`, `--animate-delay`.
- **Per-phase** `{ enter?, leave? }`: applied on the transitioning element in `before-appear` / `before-enter` / `before-leave` (overrides globals for that phase when set).
- **Class tokens:** `enterClass` / `leaveClass` may omit the `animate__` prefix; `animate__animated` is added when missing.

#### Shape (reference)

```ts
type CssTime = `${number}ms` | `${number}s`
type PhaseValue<T> = T | { enter?: T; leave?: T }

meta.transition = {
  name?: string // named CSS transition, e.g. cinematic-fade | fade-slide | fade
  enterClass?: string // animate.css enter, e.g. zoomIn or animate__zoomIn
  leaveClass?: string // animate.css leave
  duration?: PhaseValue<CssTime>
  delay?: PhaseValue<CssTime>
  appear?: boolean
  mode?: 'default' | 'out-in' | 'in-out'
}
```

#### Example (class mode + phased duration)

```ts
meta.transition = {
  enterClass: 'zoomIn',
  leaveClass: 'zoomOut',
  duration: { enter: '600ms', leave: '400ms' },
}
```
